to the top rack and move one from the top to the middle. Leave cakes to cool for 5 minutes before removing from tins. Leave to cool completely (approx. 50 minutes) on a wire rack before filling (see tip). Meanwhile, clean and dry mixing bowl."},{"isHeader":true,"content":"Cappuccino Buttercream Filling"},{"content":"Place caster sugar in mixing bowl and grind <b>20 sec\/speed 10<b>."},{"content":"Add butter, milk and 35 g coffee then beat <b>5 min\/speed 4<b>."},{"content":"Place one coffee cake on a serving plate, brush with 20 g coffee and spread with ⅓ reserved cappuccino buttercream, place second cake on top, brush with 20 g coffee and spread with ⅓ reserved cappuccino buttercream. Place last cake on top, brush with remaining 20 g coffee and spread with remaining cappuccino buttercream. Dust with cocoa powder before serving."}],"hintsAndTricks":["This cake is lovely served with iced coffee. Make a rich iced coffee, finished with some liquid caramel, and some cream.","You can use the built-in Thermomix scales to measure out the exact quantity of cake batter for each cake tin. At the end of the recipe, turn scales on, lift out mixing bowl and pour some cake batter into the prepared tin. When you return the mixing bowl to the base, it will show a minus figure indicating the weight removed <b>(- 320 g).<b>","To make the cake using one tin, choose a deep cake tin <b>(Ø 18 cm),<b> and pour in all the batter. Bake for <b>35-40 minutes<b> in a preheated oven (180°C), and leave to cool for <b>10 minutes<b> before removing from cake tin. Cool completely on a wire rack, and simply slice in three horizontally before filling.","The coffee cake can be made in advance: keep in an airtight container in the fridge for up to <b>3 days,<b> or keep for up to <b>1 month<b> in the freezer."],"basicInfo":["medium","40m","2h","12 slices"]}